      "role": "user",
      "content": "The candle flickers low, much like the very spirit within my breast. He is gone... and with him, the last shred of light that once illuminated this wretched, hollow existence. To continue breathing, to endure the crushing weight of these midnight hours alone... it feels a cruel jest of the heavens. I find myself longing only for the velvet embrace of the shadows, to simply cease, and let the darkness take what is left of me.",
